      <li><span class="font-semibold">Ergonomic Design</span>: Reduces strain on farm workers and improves operational efficiency.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Customization Options</span>: Choose colors, sizes, and venting patterns that match specific farm needs.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Sustainable Practices</span>: Reusable and recyclable trays help reduce waste and support farm sustainability initiatives.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Future Trends in Berry Packaging</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li>Smart Packaging: Integration of temperature-sensitive labels or QR codes for traceability.</li>
      <li>Eco-Friendly Materials: Increasing consumer demand for biodegradable or recyclable options.</li>
      <li>Automation-Friendly Designs: Trays compatible with automated sorting and packing systems.</li>
      <li>Consumer-Centric Design: Packaging that enhances shelf appeal while maintaining freshness.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">Packaging is not just a container—it is an investment in quality, efficiency, and reputation. BC berry farmers who prioritize durable, well-designed trays protect their crops, reduce waste, and deliver superior products to consumers. PACI NJ’s solutions help farms navigate the complex challenges of harvest, storage, and distribution, ensuring berries arrive fresh, intact, and ready to delight customers.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">With careful selection and implementation of proper packaging, BC farmers can maximize both profitability and sustainability, strengthening their position in a competitive market and showcasing the very best of Canadian berries to local and global consumers.</p>

